<p>A magnitude 6.1 earthquake struck western Turkiye late on Monday, centred near the town of Sindirgi, and was widely felt in Istanbul and the nearby provinces of Bursa, Manisa and Izmir . The tremor caused at least three buildings to collapse and prompted multiple aftershocks, but authorities reported no immediate casualties . The region had been shaken by a similar quake less than three months earlier, underscoring recurring seismic risk in the area .</p><img src='https://kagiproxy.com/img/SNgNxlKNJaRlJ0pNLr-D9HSciAgye97bCLT6fVoGP3JB0oB3jcGJJhagg_yF2Ztxv1lkuSiPRd9JaJlaD3VeRcUJLFybeW5wEjgeD5steRTT' alt='People searching through rubble following an earlier earthquake in Turkiye; file photo used to illustrate quake damage — Reuters' /><br /><h3>Highlights:</h3><ul><li>Exact timing: Turkiye’s disaster agency said the quake struck Sindirgi at 10:48 pm local time (1948 GMT) on Monday .</li><li>Aftershocks reported: The main tremor was followed by several aftershocks and was felt across multiple provinces, increasing local alarm though no casualties were immediately reported .</li><li>International solidarity: Pakistan’s foreign minister expressed solidarity and said Pakistan stood ready to provide humanitarian assistance and search-and-rescue support if needed .</li><li>Seismic context: Officials note the area is crisscrossed by geological fault lines; a separate February 2023 earthquake in southwestern Turkiye killed at least 53,000 people, highlighting the region’s vulnerability to damaging quakes .</li></ul><blockquote>Three buildings and a store that were evacuated after the last quake collapsed; there are no victims. - Interior Minister Ali Yerlikaya</blockquote><h3>Perspectives:</h3><ul><li>Turkiye disaster management agency (AFAD): The quake was felt in Istanbul and the nearby provinces of Bursa, Manisa and Izmir, according to AFAD. (<a href='https://www.thehindu.com/news/international/magnitude-61-earthquake-hits-western-turkiye-causing-buildings-to-collapse/article70210935.ece'>The Hindu</a>)</li><li>Interior Minister Ali Yerlikaya: He reported that three buildings and a store that had been evacuated after the previous quake collapsed and that there were no victims. (<a href='https://www.dawn.com/news/1951764/61-magnitude-quake-hits-western-turkiye'>Dawn</a>)</li><li>Pakistan foreign minister Ishaq Dar: Pakistan stands ready to extend humanitarian assistance and aid in search and rescue efforts; our prayers are with all those affected. (<a href='https://www.dawn.com/news/1951764/61-magnitude-quake-hits-western-turkiye'>Dawn</a>)</li></ul><h3>Sources:</h3><ul><li><a href='https://www.newarab.com/news/61-magnitude-quake-hits-western-turkey'>6.1-magnitude quake hits western Turkey</a> - newarab.com</li><li><a href='https://www.thehindu.com/news/international/magnitude-61-earthquake-hits-western-turkiye-causing-buildings-to-collapse/article70210935.ece'>Magnitude 6.1 earthquake hits western Turkiye, causing buildings to collapse</a> - thehindu.com</li><li><a href='https://www.dawn.com/news/1951764/61-magnitude-quake-hits-western-turkiye'>6.1-magnitude quake hits western Turkiye</a> - dawn.com</li><li><a href='https://www.lemonde.fr/en/international/article/2025/10/27/magnitude-6-1-quake-hits-western-turkey-causing-buildings-to-collapse_6746834_4.html'>Turkey hit by magnitude 6.1 quake, causing buildings to collapse</a> - lemonde.fr</li><li><a href='https://www.aljazeera.com/video/newsfeed/2025/10/27/magnitude-6-1-earthquake-strikes-western-turkiye'>Magnitude 6.1 earthquake strikes western Turkiye</a> - aljazeera.com</li><li><a href='https://japantoday.com/category/world/magnitude-6.1-earthquake-hits-western-turkey-damaging-buildings'>M6.1 earthquake hits western Turkey</a> - japantoday.com</li></ul>